Class Nao.ALVisionToolbox

java.lang.Object
  org.qualitune.naoservice.client.Nao.ALVisionToolbox
Enclosing class:
Nao
public class Nao.ALVisionToolbox
extends java.lang.Object

This module contains different vision functionalities, like picture taking, video recording, white balance setting, etc ... Picture and videos are both saved in /home/nao/naoqi/share/naoqi/vision.

startVideoRecord

public org.json.JSONObject startVideoRecord(java.lang.String videoname)
Start recording a video. The .avi video is stored on the robot in the /home/nao/naoqi/share/naoqi/vision folder. The record should be stopped by calling stopVideoRecord(). Resolution: 320*240, MJPG format, frame rate ~10-15 fps. Please note that only one record at a time can be made.

Parameters:
videoName - Name of the video file to be recorded.
Returns:
JSONObject which contains the following values as strings:
  • the actual return value (returnvalue)
  • exceptions (exception)
  • standard out (stdout)
  • standard err (err)

startVideoRecord_adv

public org.json.JSONObject startVideoRecord_adv(java.lang.String videoname,
                                                float framerate,
                                                java.lang.String format,
                                                int resindex,
                                                int numframes)
Start recording a video, with advanced options. Please note that only one record at a time can be made.

Parameters:
videoName - Name of the video file to be recorded.
framerate - Record frame rate [0.1-50.0]. Warning: MJPG format requires framerate greater than 2.0.
format - ARV = raw YUV422 format; IYUV = raw avi, MJPG = compressed avi.
resIndex - Resolution index. 0 = 160*120, 1 = 320*240, 2 = 640*480
numFrames - Number of frames to record. If less than 0, it records until stopVideoRecord() is called.
Returns:
JSONObject which contains the following values as strings:
  • the actual return value (returnvalue)
  • exceptions (exception)
  • standard out (stdout)
  • standard err (err)
